name: CBATTError.Code
desc: The possible errors returned by a GATT server (a remote peripheral) during Bluetooth low energy ATT transactions.

items.name: case success
items.desc: The ATT command or request successfully completed.

items.name: case invalidHandle
items.desc: The attribute handle is invalid on this peripheral.

items.name: case readNotPermitted
items.desc: The permissions prohibit reading the attribute’s value.

items.name: case writeNotPermitted
items.desc: The permissions prohibit writing the attribute’s value.

items.name: case invalidPdu
items.desc: The attribute Protocol Data Unit (PDU) is invalid.

items.name: case insufficientAuthentication
items.desc: Reading or writing the attribute’s value failed for lack of authentication.

items.name: case requestNotSupported
items.desc: The attribute server doesn’t support the request received from the client.

items.name: case invalidOffset
items.desc: The specified offset value was past the end of the attribute’s value.

items.name: case insufficientAuthorization
items.desc: Reading or writing the attribute’s value failed for lack of authorization.

items.name: case prepareQueueFull
items.desc: The prepare queue is full, as a result of there being too many write requests in the queue.

items.name: case attributeNotFound
items.desc: The attribute wasn’t found within the specified attribute handle range.

items.name: case attributeNotLong
items.desc: The ATT read blob request can’t read or write the attribute.

items.name: case insufficientEncryptionKeySize
items.desc: The encryption key size used for encrypting this link is insufficient.

items.name: case invalidAttributeValueLength
items.desc: The length of the attribute’s value is invalid for the intended operation.

items.name: case unlikelyError
items.desc: The ATT request encountered an unlikely error and wasn’t completed.

items.name: case insufficientEncryption
items.desc: Reading or writing the attribute’s value failed for lack of encryption.

items.name: case unsupportedGroupType
items.desc: The attribute type isn’t a supported grouping attribute as defined by a higher-layer specification.

items.name: case insufficientResources
items.desc: Resources are insufficient to complete the ATT request.
